title: Enable apk split per ABI, #588
message:
Enable apk split per ABI, #588

Minimize the .apk size, unpacked(compressed) from 41(17)MB to 11(7)MB
Libraries are no longer stored compressed in the .apk, so the universal apk size increses

Unfortunately, there is no way to avoid for Froyo or Debug:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27964484/android-gradle-is-use-splits-only-for-release-possible

The functionality is not enabled by default as Froyo (that should not have splits) cannot be excluded as well as builds are slower.
Set variable splitApk from commandline
.\gradlew --project-prop splitApk assembleLatestRelease

Note: When uploading to Play (and F-Droid?) the universal apk for Latest should not be included, as all abi are already included (there were at least errors reported about this)

To only enable for a few targets (and have "fat" or universal for others) set in the splits.abi closure:

      reset()
      include 'x86', 'armeabi-v7a', 'armeabi-v8a'

title: Transifex and Android Lint does not agree on plurals for Polish
message:
Transifex and Android Lint does not agree on plurals for Polish

Lint want one,few,many,other, Transifex do not accept "many".
Transifex seem to be correct, cannot suppress Transifex anyway
http://docs.translatehouse.org/projects/localization-guide/en/latest/l10n/pluralforms.html?id=l10n/pluralforms

Adopting to Transifex, suppress lint error. Handpatching in Transifex sync is a pain.
Similar to Turkish

Puzzled: Why did Turkish appear some weeks ago and Polish now?

title: Apply geoid altitude correction to WGS84 altitude (EGM96)
message:
Apply geoid altitude correction to WGS84 altitude (EGM96)

GPS elevation is reported to the Geoid, not above sea level, at least in most GPS. (For instance GENYmotion reports sea level altitude though.)
Reported elevation can be off several hundred meters.

GPS elevation is replaced with map elevation normally services, not just the offset but the reliability is poor. Sea level elevation is primarily needed if elevation is presented on the device (realtime or in graph) or used as to calibrate the barometer elevation (to be added).

There are several models for the geoid, egm96 is within 1/10 m for the reference points, better than GPS elevation accuracy.
The database is quite big. I have adopted an implementation to compress the data (both storage and RAM), basis is here https://github.com/gerhardol/EGM96/
Still adds 0.8MB to apk size, so only added to Latest build

title: Back in StartActivity for non Autostart GPS should stop gpsBoundState
message:
Back in StartActivity for non Autostart GPS should stop gpsBoundState

There is currently no way to stop the GPS if you have started GPS but do not start an actvity.
You have to remove RunnerUp from recent apps.

This change stops GPS with Back button, without exiting the app
(Home, recent apps have no effect as before).

title: Author:		gerhardol <gerhard.nospam@gmail.com>
message:
Author:		gerhardol <gerhard.nospam@gmail.com>

Author date:	1 day ago (2016-10-30 02:17:15)
Commit date:	1 day ago (2016-10-30 20:02:53)
Commit hash:	797e49b9b6e5faed762c86726306fe6619e33dff
Children:	5e236da4bb
Parent(s):	02df8d77c9

GPS (and other sensors) were not stopped when activity was stopped

On Marshmallow and later. Permissions are required to handle GPS, the check when closing was incorrect.
The solution was to ignore the check and handle the SecurityException that occurs if the user deactivates GPS permission for RunnerUp while recording an activity.

Some Lint corrections too

title: Precision was set to float before storing in SQLite
message:
Precision was set to float before storing in SQLite

SQLite REAL stores as double but double values from the GPS sensor were converted to float before storing.
This was clearly visible in the graphs, especially if playing around in Genymotion: The reported total distance did not match the graph distance

title: Repo and Travis tweaks
message:
Repo and Travis tweaks

Tweaks to Travis setup. The intention was to try to limit the build time, but most time is due to the tools/platforms-tools dependencies. Some tweaks to caches, repos at least.

Specify play versions for Wear app
Use latest Play Services for phone app. This eliminates some Minify warnings. As just play-services-wearable is specified, the app size is not inflated, as well as "multi-dex" issues with later play services.
The previous version has some "FloatMath" suppressed warnings that could be fatal...

Use Maven repo for GraphView. This eliminates some Minify warnings with later releases too.
The GraphView version is slightly updated from 3.1.0 to 3.1.4 as 3.1.0 is not available in the Maven repo. Minor changes done.
The submodule can now be removed, not used. I see no reason to customize GraphView, so no real need for the subrepo.

title: Code changes to support requesting MM permissions dynamically
message:
Code changes to support requesting MM permissions dynamically

GPS is requested at App startup. If not granted a SnackBar will nag the user (unless not ask again is ticked). (This is tricky to do when pressing Start button, the request is done asynchronously.)
A few corrections to handle GPS not started
Longer term, the GPS can be set to work like other sensors, to be able to deactivate it

Also for read/write backups. There it would be natural to always request permission, but this do not work, so popup asking the user to manually activate.

Only popup for storage permissions
The request is not working there for some reason. (This could be improved with at least supplying a link to the settings).
This should be good enough for now.

Note that sharing activities and workouts uses "internal" directories that do not require permissions.

Note: CircledImageView.setForeground() listed as added in SDK 23
Compile possible with compile SDK 22 though, seem strange that this occurs. However, few Wear should use SDK22 anyway.

title: Use AppCompat Theme
message:
Use AppCompat Theme

AppCompat theme is required for some newer elements in Support Design library like SnackBars
Using AppCompat also aligns the design with other apps, removes some of the dated look
Some overrides could be removed in code (I did not change the override in styles.xml)

The update slightly changes fonts, dividers and looks, the following "larger" changes are seen (may be more):
 * Backgrounds were previously mostly black, but not all (for instance Advanced Settings were graded). Overrides removed, all gray now
 * Before KK: Button text in manage Workouts have visual glitches when enabling/disabling, issues before too though.
 * Before KK:  CheckBoxes have slightly different appearance than stock and before

I have tried to use singleLine and various other fixes for buttons but do not find a solution that works without glitches.
I propose that visual glitches pre KK are accepted.

Note: AppCompat v22.2.1 seem to miss some functionality compared to v23. Maybe easier to improve visuals with the related SDK-24 PR too (the SDK-24 will require this PR).
Anyway, AppCompat is required to freshen up the GUI to be more standard AndroidManifest

Longer term, the app design should be updated.
Maybe Light theme?
Use more Material Design, skipping the two levels of tabs and use a action bar?

title: Prepare for Play Services update
message:
Prepare for Play Services update

No actual change. Propose it is merged so change if is available if testing for some reason - annoying to find these issues

Update Play Services requires applicationId to be set. Using a dynamic approach
The play version is not updated right now. No new api is needed what I know and updating just increases the size with 3MB (which is an issue on older devices).

title: Using latest versions of SDK tools and platform-tools
message:
Using latest versions of SDK tools and platform-tools

tools and build-tools cannot be controlled in Android. Either the SDK default is used (not specifying them in travis.yml) which often gives old versions or the latest versions from Google.
As the default are often too old the latest are used. That will too require some special setup order in the .yml.
In addition 'extras' should apparently be spelled 'extra'.

Some links:
https://github.com/codepath/android_guides/wiki/Setting-up-Travis-CI
https://github.com/travis-ci/travis-ci/issues/6193

Zephyr HxM BT checksum fix

title: Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jonasoreland/runnerup
message: Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jonasoreland/runnerup

title: Fix the Zephyr HxM Bluetooth checksum algorithm
message:
Fix the Zephyr HxM Bluetooth checksum algorithm

When using RunnerUp with a Zephyr, I was only seeing very sporadic HR values:
5 in the space of 15 minutes, that sort of thing; and no periodicity.

I guessed the checksum code was broken and sure enough it was.

This patch is to fix the Zephyr HxM Bluetooth checksum. Specifically:
 - push the checksum code down to the ZephyrHRM class
 - rather than simply XOR-ing bytes together, use the algorithm specified in
   http://www.zephyranywhere.com/zephyr-labs/development-tools/hxm-bt/communications-packet-structure-overview/

TESTED=ran in Eclipse/ADT; confirmed no parseBuffer errors; saw HR values
on the connection console in the app.

title: Fix TCX uploading to Digifit
message:
Fix TCX uploading to Digifit

For manual entries, Digifit requires a gratuitous Track with at least
one Trackpoint before it will accept the TCX. Otherwise, it silently fails
and never takes the import.

Also remove some extraneous debugging code from the DigifitUploader.

message:
Wire through the uploader into the UI

Also fix various aspects of the uploader to work with the slightly
different libraries on Android.

Upload isn't quite working; Digifit is silently refusing the TCX files
that RunnerUp generates. That's for a future investigation.
